# Raw feature collections — committing these would add ~180MB per run to git
# (51 + 38 + 90 MB across MT FWP layers #3, #10, #11). The S02.1 spec at
# docs/planning/epics/E02-geometry-ingestion.md (line 134-138) calls for
# committing both metadata + features fixtures, but assumed "small". Real MT
# data exceeds the assumption by ~3 orders of magnitude.
#
# Until a fixture-storage policy is decided (e.g. git-lfs, object-store
# upload + manifest, or sampling), keep features fixtures local-only.
# Metadata files (~7KB each) ARE committed for drift detection on field
# names, OID columns, and spatialReference.
*-features-*.geojson

# Manifests (S02.7) — *-manifest-*.json
# Per-fetch checksum manifests (~5KB each) ARE committed for cross-operator
# drift detection. Format: {features_count, layer_hash, hash_distribution,
# fetched_at, source_url, source_layer_max_record_count, source_layer_object_id_field}.
# See docs/runbooks/E02-geometry-verification.md for the manifest-diff workflow.
# No glob rule is needed here since manifests don't match *-features-*.geojson —
# this comment exists to anchor the policy.

# Atomic-write tmp files orphaned by interrupted writes (rare).
*.tmp
